# Data Layer Rules

## Golden Rule

**No data arrays or objects belong inside component files.**
If you write `const products = [...]` inside a `.jsx` file, stop and move it to `src/data/`.

## Data Files Registry

| File                                                  | Extension | Contents                                                              |
| ----------------------------------------------------- | --------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/data/products/products.js`                       | `.js`     | Product list (id: number, name, category, image, description, specs)  |
| `src/data/electricalEquipment/electricalEquipment.js` | `.js`     | Electrical equipment categories and page content                      |
| `src/data/featuredProducts/featuredProducts.js`       | `.js`     | Featured products list (id, image, title, description, href)          |
| `src/data/heroSlides/heroSlides.js`                   | `.js`     | Hero carousel slides                                                  |
| `src/data/industries/industries.js`                   | `.js`     | Industry solutions list                                               |
| `src/data/projects/projects.js`                       | `.js`     | Recent projects list                                                  |
| `src/data/partners/partners.js`                       | `.js`     | Partnership logos and descriptions                                    |
| `src/data/navigation/navigation.js`                   | `.js`     | Navbar links and dropdown structure                                   |
| `src/data/services.jsx`                               | `.jsx`    | Services list - uses `.jsx` because entries contain inline SVG icons  |
| `src/data/languages/languages.jsx`                    | `.jsx`    | Languages list - uses `.jsx` because entries contain inline SVG flags |
| `src/data/notFound/notFound.js`                       | `.js`     | 404 copy                                                              |

## Data File Format

```js
// src/data/products/products.js
export const products = [
  {
    id: 1, // number and no duplicate
    name: "Smart-Energy Meter",
    category: "LV", // 'LV' | 'MV'
    image: "/assets/images/products/smart-energy-meter.jpg",
    description: "Advanced smart energy meters...",
    specs: {
      accuracy: "Class 0.5S",
      communication: "4G/LoRa",
    },
  },
];
```

## Usage Pattern in Components

```jsx
// Correct - import from data layer
import { products } from '@/data/products/products';

export function ProductGrid({ category = 'All' }) {
  const filtered = category === 'All'
    ? products
    : products.filter(p => p.category === category);

  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-6">
      {filtered.map(product => (
        <ProductCard key={product.id} {...product} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

// Wrong - never define data inside a component
export function ProductGrid() {
  const products = [
    { name: 'Smart Meter', ... },  // <- Move this to src/data/products/products.js
  ];
}
```

## siteConfig.js - Global Site Constants

All site-level constants live in `src/config/siteConfig.js`:

- Company name
- Phone number
- Email address
- Physical address
- Social media URLs
- Copyright text

```jsx
// Correct
import { siteConfig } from '@/config/siteConfig';
<a href={`tel:${siteConfig.phone}`}>{siteConfig.phone}</a>

// Wrong - never hardcode contact info
<a href="tel:+18555XXXXXXX">+(855) XXX XXX XXX</a>
```
